ResourceManagement:
------------------

Its our appilication - handling requests for resourcees.
when gets requests from CarPlay And Apple Phone the resource manager will manage/decide whom will give the permission.

Commands for managing resources:

changeModes - request or release resources -> request or commands tells to the Phone.

modesChanged - Notification that state changes -> reply back from the phone.

play FM radio: request to take the audio resource indefinitely.

use native voice recognition: resources are return to the head uint, return resources when finished.

show backup camera: state that the screen can never be assigned to anyone else.[defining the constraints - define the rules while you are the owner. 
 1) any time - allow amy appilication to get access.
 2) user initiated - allow only user-initiated applications to get access. 
 3) never - do not let any application get access.]
 
ask siri to play music: to make a long press od push to talk siri will activate,  siri has been assigned resources and head unit is nnotified.

How the application manageing ? - application state management -  it discribe app state.
 1) TrunByTurn - Route guidence active 
 2) PhoneCall [BT call, native call, HFP call or secondary call - non carplay call]- Phone call in progress 
 3) Speech - voive intraction in progress.

During intialization session.
[ Telling to the phone ]

change mode:
Setting INIT resource mode :
Resource = mainscreen,
Trans:take,
Priority:userInitiated,
Take:userinitiated,
Borrow:anytime
BorrowId:

modes Change:
screen accessory (permnant screen accssory),
main audio accssory (permanent main audio accessory),
phone n/a,
speach n/a(none),
turns n/a,


App state:
Setting INIT App state:
Phone:NO,
Navi:YES,
Speach :NO one is speacking 


initial Modes:
 1) any high priority screen or audio is ongoing(screen: RVC , your showing call overlay,  audio: you have native cal ect...).
 
 2) any temprary medium priority(native VR , HU is in mute state, HU is announcing traffic announcement ect..) screen or audio is ongoing.
 
 3) no other screens are there. do we need to show the carplay screen immeditly after the session.
 
 This is for Head Unit telling to iPhone.
 Main Audio:
