*** when user wants to see the carplay screen from the from the requesting to HU by passing carplay icon --> requestUI();

For Screen:

 - any apple known device connected native UI screen and disconnected  , an other native screen UI played and connected again divice the last native UI screen is carplay screen - when it was  disconnected native UI screen.

For Audio:

 - any apple known device connected native UI audio and disconnected play someting on native UI audio and connected again last native UI audio will play on the carplay screen.
  
  
4 Use Cases:
  		native        carplay
  		
 audio         userInit       niceToHave
 
 screen        userInit       niceToHave
 
 
 
>>>>>>>>>>>  To work with Apple CarPlay™, accessories must support the CarPlay feature. <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<


Note: The CarPlay session is established after the user selects CarPlay.

This describes the detailed information on the changeModes/modesChanged commands that are exchanged between your CarPlay accessory and the Apple device.
This describes the changeModes request sent from your accessory to the Apple device.

1) Connection:
First Time Connection:  [Native UI(Apple Phone Screen) and CarPlay UI(CarPlay Screen) ]
when the user connects an Apple device to your CarPlay accessory for the first time.
 > Connect to an Apple device for the first time and immediately show CarPlay on the car’s display.
 > Connect to an Apple device for the first time and show a confirmation screen. After the confirmation is accepted connect CarPlay and immediately show CarPlay on the car’s display.
 > This use cases describe resource management when the user connects an Apple device to your CarPlay accessory for the first time.
 
2) Reconnection:
 > This use cases describe resource management when the user connects a known Apple device to your CarPlay accessory.
 
3) User Interaction with your Accessory:
 > This use cases describe resource management during user interactions with your accessory.
 
4) User Interaction with CarPlay:
 > This use cases describe resource management during user interactions with CarPlay.
- standby mode (display and audio off)
- a user-perceived off state (part of a power down sequence).

5) Audio Selection:
 > This use cases describe resource management during audio interactions with CarPlay.
 
6) Second Phone connection Using Bluetooth:
 > This use cases describe resource management when a second phone is connected to your accessory using Bluetooth or the accessory executes a call using any additional phone service, 
   e.g. concierge calls, etc.



>>>>>>>>>>>  To work with Apple CarPlay™, accessories must support the CarPlay feature. <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
